verses.text: For, behold, in those days , and in that time , when I shall bring again the captivity of Judah and Jerusalem ,

I will also gather all nations , and will bring them down into the valley of Jehoshaphat , and will plead with them there for my people and \add for\add* my heritage Israel , whom they have scattered among the nations , and parted my land.
And they have cast lots for my people ; and have given a boy for an harlot , and sold a girl for wine , that they might drink.

Yea, and what have ye to do with me, O Tyre , and Zidon , and all the coasts of Palestine ? will ye render me a recompence ? and if ye recompense me, swiftly \add and\add* speedily will I return your recompence upon your own head ;
Because ye have taken my silver and my gold , and have carried into your temples my goodly pleasant things :\f + \fr 3.5 \ft pleasant: Heb. desirable\f*

The children also of Judah and the children of Jerusalem have ye sold unto the Grecians , that ye might remove them far from their border.\f + \fr 3.6 \ft the Grecians: Heb. the sons of the Grecians\f*
Behold, I will raise them out of the place whither ye have sold them, and will return your recompence upon your own head :

And I will sell your sons and your daughters into the hand of the children of Judah , and they shall sell them to the Sabeans , to a people far off : for the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath spoken \add it\add*. \p
¶ Proclaim ye this among the Gentiles ; Prepare war , wake up the mighty men , let all the men of war draw near ; let them come up :\f + \fr 3.9 \ft Prepare: Heb. Sanctify\f*
Beat your plowshares into swords , and your pruninghooks into spears : let the weak say , I \add am\add* strong.\f + \fr 3.10 \ft pruninghooks: or, scythes\f*

Assemble yourselves, and come , all ye heathen , and gather yourselves together round about : thither cause thy mighty ones to come down , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 3.11 \ft cause…: or, the \+nd LORD\+nd* shall bring down\f*
Let the heathen be wakened , and come up to the valley of Jehoshaphat : for there will I sit to judge all the heathen round about.
Put ye in the sickle , for the harvest is ripe : come , get you down ; for the press is full , the fats overflow ; for their wickedness \add is\add* great.

Multitudes , multitudes in the valley of decision : for the day of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* near in the valley of decision.\f + \fr 3.14 \ft decision: or, concision, or, threshing\f*
The sun and the moon shall be darkened , and the stars shall withdraw their shining.

The 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* also shall roar out of Zion , and utter his voice from Jerusalem ; and the heavens and the earth shall shake : but the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* \add will be\add* the hope of his people , and the strength of the children of Israel.  +  r 3.16  t hope: Heb. place of repair, or, harbour *

So shall ye know that I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God dwelling in Zion , my holy mountain : then shall Jerusalem be holy , and there shall no strangers pass through her any more.\f + \fr 3.17 \ft holy: Heb. holiness\f* \p

¶ And it shall come to pass in that day , \add that\add* the mountains shall drop down new wine , and the hills shall flow with milk , and all the rivers of Judah shall flow with waters , and a fountain shall come forth of the house of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and shall water the valley of Shittim.\f + \fr 3.18 \ft flow: Heb. go\f*
Egypt shall be a desolation , and Edom shall be a desolate wilderness , for the violence \add against\add* the children of Judah , because they have shed innocent blood in their land.
But Judah shall dwell for ever , and Jerusalem from generation to generation.\f + \fr 3.20 \ft dwell: or, abide\f*
For I will cleanse their blood \add that\add* I have not cleansed : for the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* dwelleth in Zion.\f + \fr 3.21 \ft for the…: or, even I the \+nd LORD\+nd* that\f*
